==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lamarckism
<hw>La"marck"ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<ets>Lamarck</ets>, a distinguished French naturalist.]</ety>
<fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>The theory that structural variations,
characteristic of species and genera, are produced in animals and plants
by the direct influence of physical environments, and esp., in the case
of animals, by effort, or by use or disuse of certain organs. It is a
discredited theory, not believed by modern biologists.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lamasery</ent>⟦br⟧
